Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on influence maximization in social networks.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a Coordination Game model to study information propagation.
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper deals with social networks and their influence.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the hardness of influence maximization and the approximation guarantee of the greedy algorithm.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes strategies to accelerate the algorithm.
